content.description: Start Just right of Tommyknocker on a big weird crimp. The route is more of a direct climb than Tommyknocker and is really fun. A awesome way to figure out the top half of Tommyknocker.
content.location: Start on the weird crimp, the feet are weird for the start. first move reaches up to a decent sloper and moves into a layback.

content.description: This is a sit/squat start and moves to a crimp followed by a sloping crimp (hard to find), then streight up to a jug. The route is a tricky one to figure out! Definitely worth checking out!
content.location: Low start, same as mine of mine. Top out is also the same. Just stay on the face and its all fair game. Downclimb is to the left same as everything on The Big Dig.

content.description: This boulder is a decent warm up for a project close by, it has a slew of different holds/styles. Crux is a fun big move getting from the left to the right side.
content.protection: Pads, pretty good area for landing.
content.location: This problem is on the north west side of The Big Dig, and starts on the crimps.

content.description: Halfway up Barnes Butte is The Big Dig, this boulder ranges from short 10ft boulder problems to overhanging highballs. Some of the untouched rock on the north and east faces are chossy. Easiest downclimb is to the right of Mine of Mine.
